1
00:00:01,126 --> 00:00:02,961
[Mouse squeaks]

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:03,628
[Penguins chirp]

3
00:00:04,629 --> 00:00:05,630
[Screeches]

4
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:07,841
[All cheering]

5
00:00:09,885 --> 00:00:10,802
[Screeches]

6
00:00:10,886 --> 00:00:12,304
[Quacks]

7
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:14,181
J "Adventure Time" J

8
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:15,640
s Come on, grab your friends 7

9
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:18,268
J We're going to
very distant lands J

10
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,604
J With Jake the dog
and Finn the human &

11
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:22,147
J The fun will never end J

12
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:24,024
J It's "Adventure Time"“ J

13
00:00:33,096 --> 00:00:35,849
[Munching]

14
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:37,935
-[Slurps]
- Huh?

15
00:00:37,976 --> 00:00:39,436
I was just sipping my coffee.

16
00:00:39,561 --> 00:00:40,604
Oh.

17
00:00:40,729 --> 00:00:42,606
[Munching]

18
00:00:42,606 --> 00:00:44,107
[Slurps]

19
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:46,443
[Slurping and munching
rhythmically]

20
00:00:58,372 --> 00:00:59,998
[Both laugh]

21
00:01:00,082 --> 00:01:02,376
[BMO laughs]

22
00:01:03,252 --> 00:01:05,796
I am also excited about today.

23
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:07,297
Oh, yeah?

24
00:01:07,339 --> 00:01:09,967
Today is the first day
of my new job.

25
00:01:11,343 --> 00:01:12,970
What's your new job, BMO?

26
00:01:13,095 --> 00:01:14,555
Yeah, are you a spy?

27
00:01:14,596 --> 00:01:16,348
You know,
'cause of the overcoat?

28
00:01:16,431 --> 00:01:18,684
I'm a door-to-door salesman.

29
00:01:18,725 --> 00:01:19,977
- Oh.
- Oh.

30
00:01:20,060 --> 00:01:21,353
What are you selling?

31
00:01:21,353 --> 00:01:23,564
I've got so many great things.

32
00:01:23,605 --> 00:01:27,484
Like for the man about town,
this piece of lint.

33
00:01:27,568 --> 00:01:28,986
JAKE:
I'll take it.

34
00:01:29,111 --> 00:01:31,488
Hooray! My first sale!

35
00:01:31,488 --> 00:01:33,323
That'll be four doubloons.

36
00:01:33,991 --> 00:01:35,742
Can I pay you later?

37
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:38,704
Mm, the customer
is always right!

38
00:01:38,745 --> 00:01:40,706
Good attitude, BMO.

39
00:01:41,373 --> 00:01:43,625
Well, gentlemen...

40
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:45,210
got to chop that wood.

41
00:01:54,845 --> 00:01:56,138
[Whispering]
It's Ice King.

42
00:01:56,138 --> 00:01:57,639
[Whispering] I know.

43
00:01:59,141 --> 00:02:00,392
Oh!

44
00:02:04,646 --> 00:02:07,274
Okay, wish me luck, fellas,
even though I don't need --

45
00:02:07,357 --> 00:02:08,317
- Aah!
- Aah!

46
00:02:08,317 --> 00:02:10,694
-[Thud]
-[Both giggle]

47
00:02:10,777 --> 00:02:12,195


48
00:02:13,572 --> 00:02:15,824
ICE KING:
Boy, this is great, huh?

49
00:02:15,949 --> 00:02:17,909
You and me
out in the fresh air?

50
00:02:17,951 --> 00:02:20,203
Now, the key
to being a tip-top salesman

51
00:02:20,287 --> 00:02:22,164
is to get the ol' foot
in the door.

52
00:02:22,205 --> 00:02:24,333
Bodies don't talk, Ice King.

53
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,168
Well, mine does.

54
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,920
Okay, then.
If I say, "My feet hurt,"

55
00:02:28,962 --> 00:02:30,464
you can go, "Woof woof."

56
00:02:30,547 --> 00:02:32,090
That's my dogs barking.

57
00:02:32,174 --> 00:02:35,802
BMO, I think we're gonna make
an unbeatable team.

58
00:02:35,802 --> 00:02:38,305
Yeah, yeah! Let's go! Let's go!
Let's go! Let's go!

59
00:02:38,347 --> 00:02:39,473
[Laughs]

60
00:02:42,225 --> 00:02:46,855
TREE TRUNKS: "Chapter 3 --
No Time For Sleeping.

61
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:49,232
Elizabeth's heart was racing

62
00:02:49,316 --> 00:02:52,361
like a water mill
after spring thaw.

63
00:02:52,444 --> 00:02:56,615
She knew her enemies
were coming for her, but when?

64
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:59,493
Suddenly, there was a knock
at the door."

65
00:02:59,576 --> 00:03:01,244
-[Knock on door]
- Oh!

66
00:03:01,328 --> 00:03:04,956
Oh. Oh, my goodness.
[Groans]

67
00:03:04,998 --> 00:03:06,583
Someone's at the door.

68
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:08,126
That's all.

69
00:03:09,252 --> 00:03:10,379
Hello.

70
00:03:10,462 --> 00:03:12,255
Tree Trunks,
how are your children?

71
00:03:12,381 --> 00:03:14,132
Can you believe this weather?

72
00:03:16,343 --> 00:03:18,595
So polite.

73
00:03:18,637 --> 00:03:22,140
Please, please come in.

74
00:03:22,265 --> 00:03:23,767
You have a lovely home.

75
00:03:24,643 --> 00:03:26,603
Here, have some apple pie.

76
00:03:26,645 --> 00:03:28,355
Oh, thank you.

77
00:03:29,147 --> 00:03:31,108
Now, what can I do for you?

78
00:03:31,149 --> 00:03:34,027
Oh, well, I'd like to show you
what I'm selling today.

79
00:03:34,903 --> 00:03:35,779
[Grunts]

80
00:03:42,536 --> 00:03:45,288
Okay, we have a broken branch,

81
00:03:45,372 --> 00:03:46,873
a half-eaten sandwich,

82
00:03:46,915 --> 00:03:48,542
oh, another ball of lint.

83
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:49,793
TREE TRUNKS: Another?

84
00:03:49,876 --> 00:03:51,878
BMO: These are selling
like red hots.

85
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:55,799
A dust bunny -- That's like
a cage-free ball of lint.

86
00:03:55,882 --> 00:03:57,300
A doll's head,

87
00:03:57,384 --> 00:04:00,637
and a little velvet bag,
tied tight at the top.

88
00:04:00,679 --> 00:04:03,432
I'll take the branch.

89
00:04:03,432 --> 00:04:07,936
My loose cash is up there
in the flower jar.

90
00:04:08,061 --> 00:04:09,646
Help yourself.

91
00:04:10,939 --> 00:04:12,190
ICE KING: Ohh!

92
00:04:20,532 --> 00:04:23,368
-[Jar clunks]
-[Laughs]

93
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:26,538
[Both laugh]

94
00:04:26,538 --> 00:04:27,789
You have a lovely home.

95
00:04:27,914 --> 00:04:29,291
- Aah!
- Whoa!

96
00:04:29,916 --> 00:04:31,543
What'd you buy, honey bunch?

97
00:04:31,668 --> 00:04:33,044
A branch.

98
00:04:33,044 --> 00:04:34,254
Huh.

99
00:04:35,505 --> 00:04:36,923
Huh? Oh.

100
00:04:36,923 --> 00:04:40,302
Ah, Tree Trunks,
you're a financial genius.

101
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:41,678
[BMO laughs]

102
00:04:41,762 --> 00:04:44,264
I can't believe
we unloaded that branch.

103
00:04:44,306 --> 00:04:46,683
It wasn't even our best one.

104
00:04:46,767 --> 00:04:48,935
Oh, my.
Shield my eyes from the sun.

105
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,562
ICE KING: Why?

106
00:04:50,687 --> 00:04:53,315
Because I think I see
our next customer.

107
00:04:55,692 --> 00:04:57,527
Those nuts could be ours.

108
00:04:57,569 --> 00:04:59,070
Excuse me, little boy!

109
00:05:01,573 --> 00:05:03,074
How are your children?!

110
00:05:03,074 --> 00:05:04,576
Ice King, duck.

111
00:05:05,577 --> 00:05:06,912
Jump.

112
00:05:06,953 --> 00:05:08,705
Right.
Right again.

113
00:05:08,789 --> 00:05:11,082
[Laughs]
Left.

114
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,834
Jump, jump-

115
00:05:17,339 --> 00:05:19,341
Left. Right.

116
00:05:19,466 --> 00:05:20,342
Left.

117
00:05:21,843 --> 00:05:23,845
Ice King, you're doing so good.

118
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:26,181
You have not
bumped into anything.

119
00:05:26,223 --> 00:05:29,559
BMO, where's the customer?

120
00:05:29,601 --> 00:05:31,228
Oh, no.
I was so excited

121
00:05:31,353 --> 00:05:35,315
about you not bumping into
anything, I lost the customer.

122
00:05:35,357 --> 00:05:38,360
Ice King, I think we are lost.

123
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,736
[Animal howls]

124
00:05:43,824 --> 00:05:44,741
Look.

125
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,618
A house.

126
00:05:46,618 --> 00:05:49,120
ICE KING: All I see
is the inside of this coat.

127
00:05:49,871 --> 00:05:51,998
And...stop.

128
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:53,458
Knock politely.

129
00:05:54,584 --> 00:05:56,461
[Footsteps]

130
00:05:56,503 --> 00:05:57,963
[Hinges creak]

131
00:06:03,635 --> 00:06:06,638
Mysterious sentinel,
you have a lovely home.

132
00:06:06,721 --> 00:06:07,639
[Whispering]
Turn.

133
00:06:07,722 --> 00:06:08,890
[Normal voice]
How are your children?

134
00:06:09,015 --> 00:06:09,891
[Gasps]

135
00:06:20,777 --> 00:06:21,653
Hello.

136
00:06:25,866 --> 00:06:28,618
I'm a door-to-door salesman,
ma'am.

137
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:30,370
[Ice King coughs]

138
00:06:30,412 --> 00:06:33,248
[Chuckling]
Oh, excuse my indigestion.

139
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:34,666
Ouch!

140
00:06:34,666 --> 00:06:37,252
I have some wonderful
new products,

141
00:06:37,294 --> 00:06:40,046
like, uh, this ball of lint.

142
00:06:40,130 --> 00:06:42,382
No, wait,
this is the dust bunny. Uh...

143
00:06:42,424 --> 00:06:45,427
Oh, oh!
I know -- this velvet bag.

144
00:06:48,388 --> 00:06:51,892
Did I mention
that it contains Finn's teeth?

145
00:06:52,642 --> 00:06:54,644
-[Ax clatters]
Please, let's go in the parlor,

146
00:06:54,686 --> 00:06:57,439
Where we can be
more comfortable.

147
00:06:58,773 --> 00:07:01,276
And you're sure
these are Finn's teeth?

148
00:07:01,318 --> 00:07:02,277
Yes.

149
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:04,571
The same Finn
who serves Princess Bubblegum,

150
00:07:04,696 --> 00:07:07,282
obstructs my plans,
and plagues my thoughts?

151
00:07:07,324 --> 00:07:08,533
Yes.

152
00:07:08,575 --> 00:07:10,785
Finn the human's teeth.

153
00:07:10,827 --> 00:07:12,954
That's a BMO guarantee.

154
00:07:13,705 --> 00:07:15,332
ICE KING: [Whispering]
Psst! Does Finn know

155
00:07:15,415 --> 00:07:17,334
you have his teeth?
Because I don't think --

156
00:07:17,417 --> 00:07:19,461
[Whispering] Hey!
I'm trying to close a sale here.

157
00:07:20,086 --> 00:07:22,172
I hope you accept silver.

158
00:07:22,213 --> 00:07:24,716
I can pay you immediately.

159
00:07:24,841 --> 00:07:27,552
Yes, my pretties.

160
00:07:29,304 --> 00:07:30,472
Poor, little guy.

161
00:07:30,597 --> 00:07:32,098
Still wearing out
the shoe leather

162
00:07:32,182 --> 00:07:35,685
trying to make just one more
lousy sale before coming home.

163
00:07:35,727 --> 00:07:38,980
He'll feel better after we have
a little party for him.

164
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,732
Still, it's tough
seeing your kid

165
00:07:40,857 --> 00:07:43,568
get his heart set on doing
something he really sucks at.

166
00:07:43,610 --> 00:07:44,986
[Door opens]

167
00:07:47,322 --> 00:07:50,742
Hello, boys.
Meet the salesman of the year.

168
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:52,494
Or maybe of the decade.

169
00:07:53,119 --> 00:07:54,704
The Chinese food is on me.

170
00:07:54,746 --> 00:07:56,831
I mean, check out the loot.

171
00:07:56,873 --> 00:07:58,875
[Whispering]
It's real.

172
00:07:58,959 --> 00:08:01,503
What the heck did you sell
to get this silver goblet?

173
00:08:01,628 --> 00:08:05,507
Just a line of smooth talk
and pipe dreams.

174
00:08:05,507 --> 00:08:07,634
Oh, and a set
of human baby teeth.

175
00:08:07,717 --> 00:08:10,512
Where'd you even get
a set of human baby teeth?

176
00:08:11,638 --> 00:08:13,473
Human baby teeth!!

177
00:08:19,521 --> 00:08:20,647
BMO!

178
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:24,401
Branches and lint
are moving like cray, Jake.

179
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,904
Oh, sure,
I sold your baby teeth.

180
00:08:27,988 --> 00:08:29,739
I could sell any part of you.

181
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:31,908
These were, like,
the only things I had left

182
00:08:31,992 --> 00:08:33,576
from when I was a little kid.

183
00:08:35,161 --> 00:08:36,079
Hey, you know what?

184
00:08:36,162 --> 00:08:38,540
We'll just go buy back
those little pearly whites.

185
00:08:38,581 --> 00:08:40,041
I'm sure whoever bought them
is like,

186
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:41,584
"Why did I buy these things?"

187
00:08:41,668 --> 00:08:43,211
What possible use
could some guy have

188
00:08:43,336 --> 00:08:45,338
for a set of human baby teeth?

189
00:08:45,422 --> 00:08:48,925
Unless he's an evil sorcerer
or a mad scientist.

190
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,844
He wasn't a mad scientist,
was he?

191
00:08:51,594 --> 00:08:54,222
- Well...
-[Pounding on door]

192
00:09:04,482 --> 00:09:05,859
[Shrieks]

193
00:09:06,443 --> 00:09:07,694
Stay back, baby Finns.

194
00:09:07,736 --> 00:09:08,820
Aah!

195
00:09:08,862 --> 00:09:09,863
[Both scream]

196
00:09:10,488 --> 00:09:11,448
[Groans]

197
00:09:13,074 --> 00:09:13,950
[Grunts]

198
00:09:15,368 --> 00:09:18,329
They're made out of some kind
of hard tooth-like material.

199
00:09:18,371 --> 00:09:19,873
Ouch. Ouch!

200
00:09:19,873 --> 00:09:21,750
Ice King,
freeze these nightmare babies.

201
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,835
I'm not allowed
to wear my crown.

202
00:09:23,877 --> 00:09:25,462
It's against BMOQO's dress code.

203
00:09:25,503 --> 00:09:27,881
Just don't let them
climb into your mouth!

204
00:09:27,964 --> 00:09:29,340
[Groaning]

205
00:09:29,382 --> 00:09:32,385
Hey, there, bitey boys.
Get off of there.

206
00:09:32,469 --> 00:09:34,512
[Groaning]

207
00:09:34,637 --> 00:09:36,639
Where's your baby manners?
Eek.

208
00:09:36,723 --> 00:09:40,268
Hmm.
Maybe I sold too well.

209
00:09:40,351 --> 00:09:42,771
ICE KING:
Hey, you're a great salesman.

210
00:09:42,854 --> 00:09:45,398
Evil babies are not
a problem for you.

211
00:09:45,523 --> 00:09:47,525
They're an opportunity.

212
00:09:47,609 --> 00:09:49,027
Yeah.

213
00:09:49,027 --> 00:09:50,236
Where did I put those --

214
00:09:50,278 --> 00:09:52,280
Oh, here they are.

215
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:56,284
Gentlemen, could I interest you
in @ couple of sledgehammers?

216
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:59,788
Perfect for smashing through
minerals or composites.

217
00:09:59,871 --> 00:10:02,165
- I'll take one.
- Me, too!

218
00:10:02,248 --> 00:10:03,917
Great decision.

219
00:10:08,421 --> 00:10:09,422
[Poof!]

220
00:10:13,551 --> 00:10:16,054
A little tap is all it takes.

221
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,892
These baby-smashing hammers
are great.

222
00:10:20,934 --> 00:10:22,644
[Smashing]

223
00:10:27,941 --> 00:10:30,068
I'm sorry I caused such a mess.

224
00:10:30,068 --> 00:10:32,070
It's very bad for business.

225
00:10:32,946 --> 00:10:35,281
Well, time to call it a day.

226
00:10:39,452 --> 00:10:41,454
The ice man leaveth.

227
00:10:43,456 --> 00:10:45,041
BMO:
Hey, wait.

228
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:47,585
See you tomorrow...partner.

229
00:10:48,586 --> 00:10:50,588
Until tomorrow.

230
00:10:50,588 --> 00:10:52,423
Yeah, you're not
doing this tomorrow.

231
00:10:52,465 --> 00:10:55,468
[Whistling]

232
00:10:57,595 --> 00:11:01,099
Hmm. In retrospect, the attack
would have worked much better

233
00:11:01,182 --> 00:11:03,434
were they not baby teeth.

234
00:11:03,476 --> 00:11:04,978
[Clears throat]

235
00:11:07,155 --> 00:11:11,284
s Come along with me J

236
00:11:11,326 --> 00:11:15,538
J And the butterflies and bees &

237
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:20,710
This party is so crazy!

